derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 17th cent.: from cat + call, originally denoting a kind of whistle or squeaking instrument used to express disapproval at a theatre

entry.def: Catcalls are loud noises that people make to show that they disapprove of something they are watching or listening to.

example.ex: The crowd responded with boos and catcalls.
